AUGUSTA, Maine (AP) â€” Maine hunters who harvest deer with the use of muzzleloaders will start their season soon.Muzzleloaders are firearms that use projectiles that are loaded from the front end of the gun. Flintlock rifles are one example.Hunters who use muzzleloaders can do so from Nov. 29 to Dec. 11. The season is open all over the state until Dec. 4. The rest of the season is limited to a smaller area of Maine that is mostly in the southern and central parts of the state.Maine has tried to encourage more deer hunting to control the size of the herd. The traditional firearms season for deer runs until Nov. 27.